(223043, 7443, 222572, '12GAUGE', 608, '', 1319815312, '[QUOTE=Ameer;222572]I would like to ask u a question, by changing the cartridge brand n load ......... Does it affect the lead required for the upland birds? I feel that way when switching from shooting the low load (24G) of Skeet/Trap to Normal load (31G). regards[/QUOTE]\r\n\r\nYes it does. Lead is a very tricky subject. it not only differs from person to person or animal to animal or speed to speed or distance to distance. but it also differs from choke to choke and cartridge brand to brand. the only sure way is to learn the correct forward allowance by hit and trial.\r\n\r\nsomebody once told me: "think of lead as a real-time geometrical approximation involving velocities and complex angles. the calculation needs to be done in a matter of milliseconds without the use of any aid. Now who wants to learn the formula of correct lead?" lols!\r\n\r\nRegards.', 1, 1, '182.177.68.35', 0, 1, 0, 0, 0, 'on_nl2br', 0, 0),
