(224304, 5275, 172659, 'Guns_N_Roses', 1364, '', 1320582869, 'I think Taurus PT 709 Slim is a good choice for a CC weapon. Its small, light weight and really slim. It has already been reviewed by Abbas sahib on the forum. I bought it a couple of months back. When you choose to buy a weapon you have to see a lot of things, like its availability in the local market, its caliber, size, suitability for which you are choosing it, potency and finally the price. Its not the best weapon out there in CC category but considering its price it is good, roughly around 55k. Other options might be Rami or a Glock 26, but if you have more money. Its biggest advantage is its very small size. In my opinion A Baikal MP-442 or Makarov is also a very good choice for a CCW. Mak has less mag capacity whereas MP-442 has more. But in this price range the Slim beats them all. The only thing which I have found difficult to master in this gun is the trigger, and hence accuracy. But in CC I guess you do not plan on shooting at 12-15M. It would be even less than that, I think. So its a fine choice.', 1, 1, '116.71.217.212', 6, 1, 0, 0, 0, 'on_nl2br', 0, 0),
