(224260, 7519, 224206, 'Mobilinker', 170, '', 1320523774, 'Manufacturers are shifting to Polymer Frames due to cheaper Polymer Material. Polymer manufacturing, shaping, casting in to objects costs far less finances than steel or other alloy frames. For end users, Polymer Frames provide style, ergonomics, resistance to cold and rust, lesser weight etc. Moreover, manufacturers are tending towards Polymer Magazines as well.\n\nThere is a long debate about accuracy of Polymer vs All Alloy frames. Its a point of personal choice for many users. However, if accuracy and reliability in tough conditions is lower than the All Alloy frame, than top of the line manufacturers like H&K, Sig, Glock, Smith & Wesson, CZ would stick to their traditional All metal products. Again, its a long discussion resulting in very minute edge of All Alloy frames over Polymer.', 1, 1, '119.152.96.17', 0, 1, 0, 0, 0, 'on_nl2br', 0, 0),
