(227193, 5540, 227188, 'Mehdi', 5846, '', 1322025357, '@Trigger_happy78\n\nDon''t loose heart Bro. As far as I remember  I used to look for mallards towards later part of December in Nakasoo area.During this ongoing period other varieties were in abundance.Always had glorious shoots on 25th of Dec and onwards. We would stand in the boggy areas of the canal and the beaters would pull a long rope across the saroots  walking towards the guns.This would present  in coming mallards not very high  As Mallard tend to hide in the thick saroots in the day time.But beware of Boars as they are also flushed out by the rope and noise.Do carry SG/LG for them.A word of advice don''t shoot at a boar unless it is coming straight for you if you are in the bog.It is better to be on hard bank of the canal.Remember it is a Mallard Shoot and not driven Boars.  [IMG]http://www.pakguns.com/images/icons/icon7.png[/IMG]', 1, 0, '223.29.227.104', 0, 1, 0, 0, 0, 'on_nl2br', 0, 0),
