(230081, 5478, 229929, '12GAUGE', 608, '', 1323324884, '[QUOTE=Skeeter60;229929]You are right the Technies has a live swing as it has its centre of gravity a bit forward and when you start the swing it is smooth and does not need to be consciously ensured.\r\nIn the A 400 specially the 26 inch barrels the weight is slightly closer to the shoulder and one has to consciously ensure an uninterrupted smooth swing and follow through although it is mechanically very superior.[/QUOTE]\r\n\r\nSir, could it be that the rearward weight bias is due to the weight of the recoil dampening system employed in the A-400?\r\n\r\nis it possible to bring the weight forward by attaching some sort of weight in the front. for example, inserting a machined steel cartridge in the magazine tube or .\r\n\r\nwe can attach ordinary wheel balancing weights to the underside of the forend to bring the weight forward which would definitely improve the swing.\r\n\r\nRegards.', 1, 1, '39.41.25.120', 0, 1, 0, 0, 0, 'on_nl2br', 0, 0),
